32#include "nouveau_fence.h"

34#include "nv50_display.h"
35
36u64
37nv84_fence_crtc(struct nouveau_channel *chan, int crtc)
38{
39 struct nv84_fence_chan *fctx = chan->fence;
40 return fctx->dispc_vma[crtc].offset;
41}
42
43static int
44nv84_fence_emit32(struct nouveau_channel *chan, u64 virtual, u32 sequence)
45{
46 int ret = RING_SPACE(chan, 8);
47 if (ret == 0) {
48 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV11_SUBCHAN_DMA_SEMAPHORE, 1);
49 OUT_RING (chan, chan->vram.handle);
50 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_ADDRESS_HIGH, 5);
51 OUT_RING (chan, upper_32_bits(virtual));
52 OUT_RING (chan, lower_32_bits(virtual));
53 OUT_RING (chan, sequence);
54 OUT_RING (chan, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_WRITE_LONG);
55 OUT_RING (chan, 0x00000000);
56 FIRE_RING (chan);
57 }
58 return ret;
59}
60
61static int
62nv84_fence_sync32(struct nouveau_channel *chan, u64 virtual, u32 sequence)
63{
64 int ret = RING_SPACE(chan, 7);
65 if (ret == 0) {
66 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV11_SUBCHAN_DMA_SEMAPHORE, 1);
67 OUT_RING (chan, chan->vram.handle);
68 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_ADDRESS_HIGH, 4);
69 OUT_RING (chan, upper_32_bits(virtual));
70 OUT_RING (chan, lower_32_bits(virtual));
71 OUT_RING (chan, sequence);
72 OUT_RING (chan, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_ACQUIRE_GEQUAL);
73 FIRE_RING (chan);
74 }
75 return ret;
76}
77
78static int
79nv84_fence_emit(struct nouveau_fence *fence)
80{
81 struct nouveau_channel *chan = fence->channel;
82 struct nv84_fence_chan *fctx = chan->fence;
83 u64 addr = chan->chid * 16;
84
85 if (fence->sysmem)
86 addr += fctx->vma_gart.offset;
87 else
88 addr += fctx->vma.offset;
89
90 return fctx->base.emit32(chan, addr, fence->base.seqno);
91}
92
93static int
94nv84_fence_sync(struct nouveau_fence *fence,
95 struct nouveau_channel *prev, struct nouveau_channel *chan)
96{
97 struct nv84_fence_chan *fctx = chan->fence;
98 u64 addr = prev->chid * 16;
99
100 if (fence->sysmem)
101 addr += fctx->vma_gart.offset;
102 else
103 addr += fctx->vma.offset;
104
105 return fctx->base.sync32(chan, addr, fence->base.seqno);
106}
107
108static u32
109nv84_fence_read(struct nouveau_channel *chan)
110{
111 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv = chan->drm->fence;
112 return nouveau_bo_rd32(priv->bo, chan->chid * 16/4);
113}
114
115static void
116nv84_fence_context_del(struct nouveau_channel *chan)
117{
118 struct drm_device *dev = chan->drm->dev;
119 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv = chan->drm->fence;
120 struct nv84_fence_chan *fctx = chan->fence;
121 int i;
122
123 for (i = 0; i < dev->mode_config.num_crtc; i++) {
124 struct nouveau_bo *bo = nv50_display_crtc_sema(dev, i);
125 nouveau_bo_vma_del(bo, &fctx->dispc_vma[i]);
126 }
127
128 nouveau_bo_wr32(priv->bo, chan->chid * 16 / 4, fctx->base.sequence);
129 mutex_lock(&priv->mutex);
130 nouveau_bo_vma_del(priv->bo, &fctx->vma_gart);
131 nouveau_bo_vma_del(priv->bo, &fctx->vma);
132 mutex_unlock(&priv->mutex);
133 nouveau_fence_context_del(&fctx->base);
134 chan->fence = NULL;
135 nouveau_fence_context_free(&fctx->base);
136}
137
138int
139nv84_fence_context_new(struct nouveau_channel *chan)
140{
141 struct nouveau_cli *cli = (void *)chan->user.client;
142 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv = chan->drm->fence;
143 struct nv84_fence_chan *fctx;
144 int ret, i;
145
146 fctx = chan->fence = kzalloc(sizeof(*fctx), GFP_KERNEL);
147 if (!fctx)
148 return -ENOMEM;
149
150 nouveau_fence_context_new(chan, &fctx->base);
151 fctx->base.emit = nv84_fence_emit;
152 fctx->base.sync = nv84_fence_sync;
153 fctx->base.read = nv84_fence_read;
154 fctx->base.emit32 = nv84_fence_emit32;
155 fctx->base.sync32 = nv84_fence_sync32;
156 fctx->base.sequence = nv84_fence_read(chan);
157
158 mutex_lock(&priv->mutex);
159 ret = nouveau_bo_vma_add(priv->bo, cli->vm, &fctx->vma);
160 if (ret == 0) {
161 ret = nouveau_bo_vma_add(priv->bo_gart, cli->vm,
162 &fctx->vma_gart);
163 }
164 mutex_unlock(&priv->mutex);
165
166 /* map display semaphore buffers into channel's vm */
167 for (i = 0; !ret && i < chan->drm->dev->mode_config.num_crtc; i++) {
168 struct nouveau_bo *bo = nv50_display_crtc_sema(chan->drm->dev, i);
169 ret = nouveau_bo_vma_add(bo, cli->vm, &fctx->dispc_vma[i]);
170 }
171
172 if (ret)
173 nv84_fence_context_del(chan);
174 return ret;
175}
176
177static bool
178nv84_fence_suspend(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
179{
180 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv = drm->fence;
181 int i;
182
183 priv->suspend = vmalloc(priv->base.contexts * sizeof(u32));
184 if (priv->suspend) {
185 for (i = 0; i < priv->base.contexts; i++)
186 priv->suspend[i] = nouveau_bo_rd32(priv->bo, i*4);
187 }
188
189 return priv->suspend != NULL;
190}
191
192static void
193nv84_fence_resume(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
194{
195 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv = drm->fence;
196 int i;
197
198 if (priv->suspend) {
199 for (i = 0; i < priv->base.contexts; i++)
200 nouveau_bo_wr32(priv->bo, i*4, priv->suspend[i]);
201 vfree(priv->suspend);
202 priv->suspend = NULL;
203 }
204}
205
206static void
207nv84_fence_destroy(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
208{
209 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv = drm->fence;
210
211 nouveau_bo_unmap(priv->bo_gart);
212 if (priv->bo_gart)
213 nouveau_bo_unpin(priv->bo_gart);
214 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &priv->bo_gart);
215 nouveau_bo_unmap(priv->bo);
216 if (priv->bo)
217 nouveau_bo_unpin(priv->bo);
218 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &priv->bo);
219 drm->fence = NULL;
220#ifdef __NetBSD__
221 linux_mutex_destroy(&priv->mutex);
222#else
223 mutex_destroy(&priv->mutex);
224#endif
225 kfree(priv);
226}
227
228int
229nv84_fence_create(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
230{
231 struct nvkm_fifo *fifo = nvxx_fifo(&drm->device);
232 struct nv84_fence_priv *priv;
233 u32 domain;
234 int ret;
235
236 priv = drm->fence = kzalloc(sizeof(*priv), GFP_KERNEL);
237 if (!priv)
238 return -ENOMEM;
239
240 priv->base.dtor = nv84_fence_destroy;
241 priv->base.suspend = nv84_fence_suspend;
242 priv->base.resume = nv84_fence_resume;
243 priv->base.context_new = nv84_fence_context_new;
244 priv->base.context_del = nv84_fence_context_del;
245
246 priv->base.contexts = fifo->nr;
247 priv->base.context_base = fence_context_alloc(priv->base.contexts);
248 priv->base.uevent = true;
249
250#ifdef __NetBSD__
251 linux_mutex_init(&priv->mutex);
252#else
253 mutex_init(&priv->mutex);
254#endif
255
256 /* Use VRAM if there is any ; otherwise fallback to system memory */
257 domain = drm->device.info.ram_size != 0 ? TTM_PL_FLAG_VRAM :
258 /*
259 * fences created in sysmem must be non-cached or we
260 * will lose CPU/GPU coherency!
261 */
262 TTM_PL_FLAG_TT | TTM_PL_FLAG_UNCACHED;
263 ret = nouveau_bo_new(drm->dev, 16 * priv->base.contexts, 0, domain, 0,
264 0, NULL, NULL, &priv->bo);
265 if (ret == 0) {
266 ret = nouveau_bo_pin(priv->bo, domain, false);
267 if (ret == 0) {
268 ret = nouveau_bo_map(priv->bo);
269 if (ret)
270 nouveau_bo_unpin(priv->bo);
271 }
272 if (ret)
273 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &priv->bo);
274 }
275
276 if (ret == 0)
277 ret = nouveau_bo_new(drm->dev, 16 * priv->base.contexts, 0,
278 TTM_PL_FLAG_TT | TTM_PL_FLAG_UNCACHED, 0,
279 0, NULL, NULL, &priv->bo_gart);
280 if (ret == 0) {
281 ret = nouveau_bo_pin(priv->bo_gart, TTM_PL_FLAG_TT, false);
282 if (ret == 0) {
283 ret = nouveau_bo_map(priv->bo_gart);
284 if (ret)
285 nouveau_bo_unpin(priv->bo_gart);
286 }
287 if (ret)
288 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &priv->bo_gart);
289 }
290
291 if (ret)
292 nv84_fence_destroy(drm);
293 return ret;
294}
